case-organizer (4.2.0) stable; urgency=high

  * Deleted the legacy 9-tool server-side PDF suite (~1,800 lines of dead
    code including all routes, helpers, templates, and static JS). The
    client-side BentoPDF suite at /bento/ replaces it entirely.
  * Reorganised and overhauled app.py: consolidated into 17 logical sections,
    replaced print() with logging, DRY'd duplicated error handlers, and added
    comprehensive inline comments. Net reduction of ~2,000 lines.
  * Fixed subsequent bugs introduced by the overhaul across BentoPDF
    integration, CSP headers, dropdown components, and form logic.

 -- Izumi <swarajswarupaggarwal@gmail.com>  Thu, 19 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0530

case-organizer (4.1.0) stable; urgency=high

  * Added session cookie security flags (HttpOnly, SameSite) to harden
    authentication handling.
  * Added standard security response headers including CSP and
    X-Frame-Options.
  * Removed hardcoded debug=True and enforced proper production configuration.
  * Implemented persistent login sessions (Gmail-style) with 30-day duration,
    database-backed storage, and sliding expiry.
  * Added comprehensive automated test suite (75 tests passing).
  * Prepared production WSGI server configuration using waitress.
  * Fully addressed datetime.utcnow() deprecation across the codebase.
  * Enforced authentication checks across all API routes including /api/years,
    /api/months, /api/cases, /api/cases/search, and /create-case.
  * Replaced stdout path printing with proper logging mechanisms.
  * Removed silent exception handling and introduced explicit error logging.
  * Added systemd service sandboxing for improved process isolation.
  * Resolved minor thread-safety issues in timer variables.

 -- Izumi <swarajswarupaggarwal@gmail.com>  Wed, 18 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0530

case-organizer (4.0.3) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added Court/Forum selection to Case Law (Supreme Court, Federal Court,
    Privy Council, High Court with searchable dropdown for all current and
    historical Indian High Courts).
  * Added structured citation system with support for INSC, SCC, SCC Online,
    SCR, and AIR journal formats, replacing free-text citation input.
  * Added Edit Case Law form (via View/Edit Note) allowing full metadata
    editing including court, citations, classification, and notes.
  * Added migration logic to parse existing free-text citations into
    structured rows; legacy citations shown with banner for manual correction.
  * Added new API endpoints: GET /case-law/courts, GET /case-law/<id>/detail,
    PUT /case-law/<id>/edit for court data, full case detail, and metadata
    editing respectively.
  * Added Citation search tab in Search Case Law, querying the normalized
    case_law_citations table by journal, year, volume, and page.
  * Replaced all native <select> dropdowns (except Advanced Search bar) with
    custom Long-List Dropdown component for consistent styling and controlled
    scroll height across light and dark themes.
  * Replaced "We're Representing" dropdown in Create Case with tab-style
    toggle buttons (Petitioner / Respondent).
  * Added auto flip-up positioning for dropdown panels when near the bottom
    of the viewport, preventing page scroll push-down.
  * Added bidirectional year sync between Decision Year and citation row year
    fields; new citation rows auto-populate year from existing context.
  * Enforced integer-only input on citation Year, Volume, and Page/Entry
    fields via keydown filtering, paste validation, and input sanitization.
  * Added "Constitutional" sub-type to Commercial cases on both Create Case
    and Case Law sides.

 -- Izumi <swarajswarupaggarwal@gmail.com>  Tue, 17 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0530

case-organizer (4.0.2) stable; urgency=high

  * Improved Note.json edit modal layout by tightening field spacing and
    reducing scrollbar interference with note textarea controls.
  * Added a left-edge resize handle for Case Notes and Case Law note textareas,
    while keeping native bottom-right resize support.
  * Increased default note editor textarea height and constrained Create Case
    "Additional Notes" resizing to stay within form bounds.
  * Added "Office Reports" as a Manage Case subcategory (alongside
    Orders/Judgments and Primary Documents) for Criminal, Civil, and Commercial.
  * Standardized invoice date handling to DD-MM-YYYY in UI and backend, with
    validation/normalization at save time.
  * Increased generated invoice top margin by an additional inch to better fit
    larger printed letterheads.
  * Added AFK-aware session keepalive so active typing/editing and in-browser
    processing no longer trigger premature auto logout.

 -- Izumi <swarajswarupaggarwal@gmail.com>  Thu, 20 Feb 2025 15:00:00 +0530

case-organizer (4.0.1) stable; urgency=high

  * Fixed Manage Case uploads returning "Bad JSON" for large/merged PDFs in
    deployed environments by hardening upload handling and response paths.
  * Added JSON-safe upload error handling for /manage-case/upload and
    /case-law/upload (400/413/500), with clearer operator-facing diagnostics.
  * Removed Flask/Werkzeug body-size caps for uploads and introduced dedicated
    upload spooling via CASEORG_UPLOAD_TMP_DIR.
  * Updated Debian defaults to use /var/lib/case-organizer/upload_spool for
    upload temp storage.
  * Fixed homepage horizontal overflow that created a blank scrollable area on
    the right side of the UI.
  * Added markdown rendering for Case Notes ("Additional Notes") and Case Law
    notes ("Brief/Note") in the UI, while keeping existing JSON note storage.
  * Extended markdown rendering to the Search Case Law preview card ("Note
    preview") and preserved markdown structure in generated note summaries.
  * Fixed duplicate/raw preface text above markdown previews in Search Case Law
    by removing note-text fallback from `text_preview` and hiding empty snippets.

 -- Izumi <swarajswarupaggarwal@gmail.com>  Tue, 17 Feb 2026 18:30:00 +0530

